summary: Saudade - Short Snufkin fic   Saudade: Portuguese word that means: 1) desire; 2) the thought of something that has happened and...
body:
Saudade - Short Snufkin fic 

Saudade: Portuguese word that means: 1) desire; 2) the thought of something that has happened and you don’t have it now; nostalgia; 3) long for someone who isn’t near. (Also english is not my first language so be kind)

Was that a stomaachache? A flu? Some weird parasite who made him feel weird and heavy like he wanted to sink into the ground? Snufkin didn’t knew.
There was a cold breeze going into the leafs and making them sound like better times.
He felt so……… solitary.
His stomach seemed to turn into a knot and his throat tightened.
What is this? Does my body needs more rest?
He remembered Moominmama and how she probably would check his temperature, and how moomin would make him stay laid down until he felt better. The tightness got worse.
Snufkin tucked himself better into the blanket and tried to put himself to sleep. He could not sleep.
I must be sick somehow. I never felt like this. He thought, trying to get rid of some tears that were forming. He just wanted to sleep to continue his journey.
He stared into the sky and saw a thousand of stars. He thought of Moominvalley.
He sighed heavily, trying to cover himself better with the blanket.
Snufkin missed them all so much. He just didn’t felt like admiting so soon that someone as free as him would need someone.
But gosh, he missed his family so much.
He missed Moomin, so, so much.
And he slept, still with his heart heavy on the chest.
